-- China Sunergy Wins 120-Megawatt Contract for Solar Power Plant in Italy
-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   M a r t i n
-- 2010-12-17T15:34:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-17/china-sunergy-wins-120-megawatt-solar-power-contract-in-italy.html
China Sunergy Co. , a manufacturer of
solar power cells, won a contract to supply 120 megawatts of
modules to Ecoware SpA for projects in Italy.  China Sunergy will make the first deliveries this year and
expects to complete the order in the third quarter of next year,
the Nanjing, China-based company said today in a statement.
China Sunergy said it has won orders for 600 megawatts of
modules for delivery during 2011.  China Sunergy rose as much as 12 cents and traded at $4.37,
up 2 cents, as of 10:32 a.m. in Nasdaq Stock Market trading. The
shares have decreased 5.4 percent this year. Closely held
Ecoware is based in Padova, Italy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Christopher Martin  in New York at 
 cmartin11@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net . 